The paper proposes a novel technique for program synthesis using neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach involves the use of neural modules for input-output processing and program synthesis, which are trained using machine learning techniques such as backpropagation, making it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing neural architectures for program induction, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the proposed approach involves the synthesis of computer programs for string transformations, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
